HEADWORD: Eschynite
<hw>Es"chy*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
shame.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A rare mineral, containing chiefly
niobium, titanium, thorium, and cerium. It was so called by Berzelius on
account of the inability of chemical science, at the time of its
discovery, to separate some of its constituents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Escocheon</ent>⟦br⟧
